<h2>Mailinglist</h2>

<p>
The SysDB mailinglist is the central place for announcements, discussion, and
development issues. Please use it for any questions, comments, or suggestions
you may have.
</p>

<h3>Subscribe to / unsubscribe from the list</h3>

<p>
To subscribe to the list, send an email to <a
href="mailto:sysdb+subscribe@sysdb.io">sysdb+subscribe@sysdb.io</a>. You will
then receive a confirmation request to the email address you sent the mail
from. To unsubscribe, send an email to  <a
href="mailto:sysdb+unsubscribe@sysdb.io">sysdb+unsubscribe@sysdb.io</a>
</p>

<h3>Post to the list</h3>

<p>
Anybody may post to the list by sending email to <a
href="mailto:sysdb@sysdb.io">sysdb@sysdb.io</a>. In order to protect ourselves
against spam, non-member posts are held back for manual approval, though.
</p>

<h3>Further commands</h3>

<p>
To receive a summary of all available commands, send an email to <a
href="mailto:sysdb+help@sysdb.io">sysdb+help@sysdb.io</a>. You will get back
an email with more details.
</p>

